# EEex Remote Console — Claude Code Context

Copy this to `CLAUDE.md` and customize for your setup.

## Project Overview

File-based IPC bridge for executing Lua inside a running BG:EE/BG2:EE game with EEex (protocol 1.1). Two files in the game's override directory serve as the communication channel: a command file (Lua source, optionally prefixed with `--@` directive comments) and a result file (JSON).

## Key Files

- `eeexremote/M_EEexRC.lua` — in-game module (polls for commands, executes them under a watchdog, writes JSON results; protocol 1.1)
- `eeexremote/EEexRC.menu` — invisible 1x1 menu element that fires `EEexRemote.Poll()` every render frame (pushed on both the world screen and the main menu)
- `tools/eeex-remote.sh` — bash CLI (exit codes: 0 ok / 1 Lua or parse error / 2 timeout / 3 usage)
- `tools/eeex-remote.ps1` — PowerShell CLI (same exit codes; `-Api` is the pwsh-File-safe way to list globals)
- `tools/scripts/` — canned Lua scripts: `ping.lua` (liveness + capabilities), `list-api.lua` (API surface overview), `party.lua` (party names)
- `tools/smoke-test.ps1` — in-game test suite (needs a running game on the world screen)
- `setup-eeexremote.tp2` — WeiDU installer (EEex presence check + LuaJIT ini gate)

## Game Directory

Set this to your game's install path:

```
GAME_DIR=/path/to/Baldurs Gate II Enhanced Edition
OVERRIDE=$GAME_DIR/override
```

PowerShell equivalent:

```powershell
$override = "C:\path\to\Baldurs Gate II Enhanced Edition\override"
```

## Quick Test

```bash
tools/eeex-remote.sh "$OVERRIDE" 'print("hello")'
```

```powershell
.\tools\eeex-remote.ps1 $override 'print("hello")'
```

