## EEex Gotchas

- EEex exposes no version global — probe for capabilities (function presence, `jit`, `io`/`os`) instead of checking versions
- The Lua `io`/`os` libraries only exist with the EEex LuaJIT component (v1.0.0: "Experimental" tier; 0.10/0.11: "Experimental - Use LuaJIT")
- `EEex_Menu_LoadFile("Name")` for .menu files, NOT `Infinity_DoFile`
- The after-main-file-loaded listener fires again on every F5 UI reload; menus are rebuilt from source, so re-hooking there is correct and does not stack
- Windows `os.rename` fails if the target exists — `os.remove` the target first when publishing atomically
- LuaJIT count hooks don't fire inside compiled traces — `jit.off()` before `debug.sethook` watchdogs, `jit.on()` after
- Each Lua `:gsub()` call must be on a separate statement (chaining passes count as arg)
- No `Infinity_DisplayString()` at M_ load time — engine display not ready
- `print()` output goes to EEex console, use `Infinity_DisplayString()` for in-game display
